ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the PR. Let me also check
a few more things to complete my analysis:\n\n1. Check if there are any migratio
ns for match_actions, matches, conversations tables\n2. Check the blocks entity 
path\n3. Check if there are existing design-system tests/golden files\n4. Check 
if there\'s an api-contract for matching\n\nLet me also verify a few more issues
I noticed:\n- The BlockEntity is imported from `../blocks/block.entity` but I sh
ould verify if this path is correct\n- No migrations were found for the new tabl
es (match_actions, matches, conversations, conversation_participants)\n- The `qu
eryCandidatesFromDb` method in matching.service.ts has a potential SQL injection
concern (though it uses parameterized queries)\n- The `MatchingBloc` test only h
as 3 tests and doesn\'t cover match creation, failure cases, or external match r
eceived\n- The `MatchingService` test doesn\'t cover `getMatchSummary`, cache co
rruption, lock contention, empty profile, etc.\n- The `SwipeActionDto` allows `s
uper_like` but PRD only mentions `like` and `pass`\n- In `matching.controller.ts
`, the `getMatchSummary` is called with `user.userId` but the `matchingService.g
etMatchSummary` takes `matchId` and `forUserId`. Looking at the controller, it g
ets `result.matchId` and passes it correctly.\n- The `MatchingGateway` emits `ma
tch:created` to both users, but the controller only emits to `userAId` (actor) a
nd `userBId` (target). Looking at the controller code more carefully: `this.matc
hingGateway.emitMatchCreated(user.userId, dto.target_id, ...)` - this passes the
actor and target, but the gateway emits to both. However, the payload is `summar
yA` which is from the actor\'s perspective. The `matched_user` in the payload wo
uld be the target for actor, but for the target, `matched_user` should be the ac
tor. This is a bug!\n- In `matching.controller.ts`, when a mutual match is creat
ed, `summaryA` is fetched from the actor\'s perspective. Then the same payload i
s sent to both users. This means both users receive the same `matched_user` data
- the target\'s profile. The target should receive the actor\'s profile as `matc
hed_user`.\n- The `MatchingBloc` uses `Map<String, dynamic>` for cards and match
data instead of typed models. This violates the Flutter coding standard that say
s "禁止使用 `dynamic` 传递 API 数据".\n- In `home_page.dart`, `_buildActionButto
ns` passes `onTap` to `SwActionButton` but `SwActionButton` uses `onTapDown` int
ernally. The `HomePage` calls `_submitSwipe` via `onTap` callback which is a `Vo
