ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the PR. Let me compile my
findings and write the review report.\n\nKey findings:\n\n**Blocking issues:**\n
1. **Missing Database Migrations** - The PR introduces new entities (`MatchActio
nEntity`, `MatchEntity`, `ConversationEntity`, `ConversationParticipantEntity`) 
but no migration files were created. With `synchronize: false` in the TypeORM co
nfig, the database schema won\'t be updated and the application will fail. Per `
nestjs.md`: "Agent 修改 Entity 后，必须同时生成并提交 Migration 文件".\n2. **Soc
ket.io Payload Bug** - In `matching.controller.ts`, when a mutual match is creat
ed, `getMatchSummary` is called with the actor\'s `userId`, which returns `match
ed_user` as the target. The same payload is emitted to both users via `matchingG
ateway.emitMatchCreated`. This means the target user receives a payload where `m
atched_user` is themselves, not the actor. According to PRD v1-matching.md: "Pay
load 包含 `match_id`、`conversation_id`、`matched_user` 资料摘要" - the `matched
_user` should be the OTHER user for each recipient.\n3. **No ProfileCompletionGu
ard** - PRD v1-profile.md requires "后端 JWT Guard 之后增加 `ProfileCompletionGu
ard`" and "未完善资料的用户调用 `GET /matching/recommendations` 或 `POST /matchi
ng/actions` 时，统一返回 `code=1000`". The current implementation only checks pr
ofile completeness in `getRecommendations` service method (returns empty array),
but doesn\'t return code=1000. Also `POST /matching/actions` doesn\'t check prof
ile completeness at all. This is a requirement from the PRD.\n\n**Major issues:*
*\n4. **No Typed Models in Mobile** - The Flutter code uses `Map<String, dynamic
>` extensively in `MatchingBloc`, `MatchingRepository`, and states. This violate
s `flutter.md` line 461: "禁止使用 `dynamic` 传递 API 数据". Models should use `
freezed` + `json_serializable`.\n5. **Incomplete Test Coverage** - `MatchingBloc
` test only covers 3 basic scenarios. Missing: match creation flow, error handli
ng, external match received. `MatchingService` tests miss: `getMatchSummary`, ca
che corruption, lock contention, profile incomplete with code 1000, etc.\n6. **C
ursor Pagination Bug in MatchListCubit** - When fetching more matches with a cur
sor, the cubit replaces the entire list instead of appending. This breaks infini
te scroll behavior.\n7. **Maestro E2E Limitations** - The swipe flow `swipe_reco
mmendations.yaml` only tests mode tab switching and pass button. It doesn\'t act
ually test the swipe gesture (which Maestro can do with `swipe`). Also the `asse
rtVisible: "首页"` in the flow assumes the BottomNavigationBar label is visible,
but `HomePage` doesn\'t have an AppBar with "首页" title.\n8. **API Contract Mis
match** - `docs/api-contracts/matching.yaml` uses `superlike` (without underscor
e) in the enum, but `SwipeActionDto` allows `super_like` (with underscore). Also
the OpenAPI contract doesn\'t define the `GET /matches` endpoint or the `match:c
reated` socket event response schema.\n9. **No Golden Tests for New Design Syste
m Components** - The PR adds 5 new design system components but no golden tests 
were added to `packages/design-system/test/`. Per `testing.md`: "新增/修改的 `pa
ckages/design-system` 组件" requires "Widget test + Golden test".\n10. **Missing
`ProfileCompletionGuard` Implementation** - The PRD requires `ProfileCompletionG
uard` on matching APIs, but it\'s not implemented. The service-level check in `g
etRecommendations` returns `[]` instead of `code=1000`.\n\n**Minor issues:**\n11
. `BottomNavigationBar` in `app.dart` uses `onTap` instead of custom `GestureDet
ector` with `onTapDown` - but this is a Material component, so Maestro compatibi
lity might still work via the tab label. Not a major issue.\n12. `MatchListPage`
empty state uses raw `Icons.chat_bubble_outline` instead of a design-system icon
component - minor.\n13. `docs/modules/matching.md` mentions `RecommendationCard`
and `MatchSummary` as typed classes in the BLoC pseudocode, but actual code uses
`Map<String, dynamic>`. Documentation is slightly inconsistent with implementati
on.\n14. `SwipeActionDto` allows `super_like` but the PRD v1-matching.md only me
ntions `like` and `pass` in the technical requirements. MVP scope doesn\'t inclu
de super_like.\n\nLet me now write the review report.',
    encrypted=None
)
